    <title>Adjusting Sensor Actions and Audit Intervals</title>
    <shortdesc>You can configure audit intervals and actions for groups of
        sensors.</shortdesc>
    <prolog><author/>
        <author/>
    </prolog>
    <body>
        <context id="context_N1001E_N1001B_N10001">
            <p><draft-comment author="jowens">US64069 new
                    topic</draft-comment>For more information about sensors and sensor groups, see
                    <xref href="jow1443819549360.xml"/>.</p>
            <p>To use the command-line interface, see <xref href="jow1443819706243.xml"/>.</p>
        </context>
        <steps id="steps_zdg_53f_4t">
            <step conref="jow1426453628262.xml#jow1426453628262/step_N1002B_N10028_N1001C_N10001" id="step_N10047_N10043_N1001F_N10001">
                <cmd/>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10056_N10040_N1001F_N10001">
                <cmd>Select the <uicontrol>Sensors</uicontrol> tab.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10063_N10040_N1001F_N10001">
                <cmd>In the <codeph>Sensor Groups</codeph>
                    list, click <uicontrol>Edit SensorGroup</uicontrol> for the
                    group you want to configure. </cmd>
                
                    <fig id="fig_nlk_pjf_4t">
                        <image href="jow1443885204993.image" id="image_qwz_3kf_4t">
                            <alt>TiS Edit SensorGroup</alt>
                        </image>
                    </fig>
                    <p>In the <wintitle>Edit SensorGroup</wintitle> dialog box, change the settings
                        as required.</p>
                    <dl>
                        <dlentry>
                            <dt>Audit Interval</dt>
                            <dd>
                                <p>The time, in seconds, to wait between sensor
                                    audits. At each audit, the sensor status reading is refreshed.
                                    Changes to the audit interval do not take effect until the
                                    current interval expires.</p>
                            </dd>
                        </dlentry>
                        <dlentry>
                            <dt>Sensor Group Critical Actions</dt>
                            <dd>
                                <p>The action to take if the sensor status is
                                        <codeph>Critical</codeph>. If this
                                    is set to <codeph>Alarm</codeph>, then
                                    when this status is reported, a corresponding HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade
                                    alarm is generated, and the host availability is set to
                                        <codeph>Degraded</codeph>. </p>
                            </dd>
                        </dlentry>
                        <dlentry>
                            <dt>Sensor Group Major Actions</dt>
                            <dd>
                                <p>The action to take if the sensor status is
                                        <codeph>Major</codeph>. If this is
                                    set to <codeph>Alarm</codeph>, then
                                    when this status is reported, a  corresponding HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade
                                    alarm is generated, and the host availability is set to
                                        <codeph>Degraded</codeph>.</p>
                            </dd>
                        </dlentry>
                        <dlentry>
                            <dt>Sensor Group Minor Actions</dt>
                            <dd>
                                <p>The action to take if the sensor status is
                                        <codeph>Minor</codeph>. If this is
                                    set to <codeph>Alarm</codeph>, then
                                    when this status is reported,  a  corresponding HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade
                                    alarm is generated.</p>
                            </dd>
                        </dlentry>
                    </dl>
                
            </step>
        </ol>
    </body>
</task-wr>